      "date": "2016-01-28 05:37:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Because it will do llog_init_handle(), which includes osp_attr_get,\n > before transaction stop (object is created).  So llog_init_handle\n > will return -ENOENT here.\n\nI'd think that osp_object_create() should leave some sign in the object?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "387e291f7eaf242cd72f186d33f6779e8d765626",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2016-01-28 07:42:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified+1\n\nTests uploaded by Onyx Autotest from onyx-36vm1 for review-dne-part-2 received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.7/x86_64: (https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/9e9ca170-c592-11e5-b4e1-5254006e85c2). Ran 13 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a924e127171a2b0fcae5a57cc1f2862de033c19f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2016-01-28 18:18:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n\"I'd think that osp_object_create() should leave some sign in the object?\"\n \nYes, indeed, but it is unsafe to use that object. Besides the object might be reset to non-exist anytime. I would prefer to create the object first. then initialize the llog based on that.\n\nActually I found this problem during my local double MDT failover test. unfortunately I am not able to catch the debug log to see why the object is marked non-exist after object create. Though IMHO, we prefer this way for now, until we can better \"control\" those remote object flags. \n\nBtw: this does not resolve LU-7564 totally, still investigate the real reason yet.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ff6ffde90ed7b5224439e0c6c095cb4e8ba77d03",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2016-01-28 18:23:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\npersonally I find this practice very risky - there is the API and expectations behind that. our primary goal is not to workaround a problem by some means. at least we need to understand the root cause in details. if The Right Solution is not possible at moment, then sure, go for a workaround, file a debt ticket, etc.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
